# Project Memory

At the start of any non-trivial task on this repo, read [memory.md](mdc:memory.md) first.
It is the fast-refresh source of truth (live state, key decisions, gotchas, open TODOs).
The longer prose docs live in [README.md](mdc:README.md).

## Keeping memory.md current

Update `memory.md` after any change that affects how the project works, including:

- A new page, integration, dependency, or build/deploy change.
- A key decision or trade-off (and *why*) — append to the Decisions section.
- A new gotcha you hit (and how you resolved it).
- Completing or adding a TODO — keep the Open TODOs list accurate.

Rules of thumb:

- Keep it concise and skimmable (lists over prose). It is a cheat sheet, not a tutorial.
- Record intent and *why*, not a play-by-play of edits.
- If a fact in `memory.md` or `README.md` is now wrong, fix it in the same change — never leave stale state.
- Do not duplicate large content between `memory.md` and `README.md`; link instead.
